## 8) State Model (Must implement)

### 8.1 Global states
- `authState`: `checking | unauthenticated | authenticated`
- `roleState`: `student | instructor | technician | iiw_instructor | iiw_admin | super_admin`
- `uiLang`: `tr | en`
- `networkState`: `idle | loading | error`

### 8.2 User app local states
- `activeTab`
- `equipmentCategory`
- `equipmentSearch`
- `equipmentCart`
- `studioSelection`
- `studioWeekCursor`
- `bookingWarnings`

### 8.3 Admin app local states
- `activeAdminPage`
- `pendingCount`
- `adminStudioWeekStart`
- `adminStudioSelectedSlot`
- `trafficFilterDate`
- `quickCheckoutCart`

---

## 9) Responsive Rules

- Mobile-first breakpoints: `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`.
- Inputs on small screens must stay >=16px font.
- Sidebar remains scrollable while header fixed.
- Main content keeps `min-h-0` where needed to prevent overflow bugs.
- Sticky utility bars only where useful (nav/filter).

---

## 10) Accessibility Rules

- All icon-only buttons need `aria-label`.
- Modals: `role="dialog"` + `aria-modal="true"`.
- Keyboard focus visible (ring with red tint).
- Color contrast for primary CTA text always WCAG-compliant.
- Use semantic headings and form labels.

---

## 11) Interaction Rules

- Any async button gets loading/disabled state.
- Avoid duplicate in-flight requests for same data block.
- Show inline error state for failed fetch.
- Show empty states with actionable hint text.
- Keep toast feedback for success/error short and clear.

---

## 12) Build Output Requirements

Return:
1. `UserApp` page implementation
2. `AdminApp` page implementation
3. `components/*` set
4. `styles/tokens` or utility contract
5. `mockData.ts` with realistic fixture data
6. `README` explaining component map and page composition

Do not output pseudocode. Output concrete UI code.

---

## 13) Acceptance Checklist (Done when all true)

- [ ] Brand red usage matches primary actions and highlights.
- [ ] User app has OTP overlay and reserve-home card grid.
- [ ] Admin shell has fixed header + left sidebar + multi-page views.
- [ ] Studio weekly calendar exists in both user and admin contexts.
- [ ] Buttons/inputs/cards follow rounded + border + shadow system.
- [ ] `font-black` emphasis appears in headers and key labels.
- [ ] Mobile and desktop both visually coherent.
- [ ] Modal, toast, loading, empty, error states present.

---

## 14) Optional “Strict Match” Add-on Prompt

If the model supports screenshot-to-code or iterative refinement, append:

"After first pass, run a second pass to increase visual density and tighten spacing to match a mature production Tailwind app: smaller meta typography, stronger uppercase micro-labels, more explicit borders, and controlled card shadows. Keep red accents constrained to primary interactions and semantic warnings."

